    "body_en": "<p>The U.S. National Science Foundation Directorate for Technology, Innovation and Partnerships on Friday announced the launch of a new initiative designed to launch and scale a new generation of independent research organizations. These…</p><p>The field has been building toward moments like this. Cosmology is currently in a productive tension: precision surveys are returning data detailed enough to test the standard model in ways not previously possible.</p><p>Independent observations will now determine how well the result holds under different conditions. The key question now is whether the effect holds when confronted with other surveys, tighter systematics controls, and independent calibrations.</p><p class=\"art-source\"><a href=\"https://www.nsf.gov/news/nsf-announces-new-initiative-launch-scale-new-generation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Source</a></p>",
